Java Assignment: Errors and Exceptions 
Here are the answers to your assignment questions regarding Java's error-handling mechanism. 
1. Different Types of Errors in Java Errors in Java are generally classified into three categories: 

• Compile-time Errors: Syntax mistakes (e.g., missing semicolons) caught by the compiler before the program runs. 
• Runtime Errors: Occur during execution, often due to logic issues or environmental factors (e.g., dividing by zero). 
• Logical Errors: The program runs without crashing but produces incorrect results because the code's logic is flawed. 

2. What is an Exception?
An Exception is an event that occurs during the execution of a program that disrupts the normal flow of instructions.
It is an object which is thrown at runtime when an unexpected condition arises. 
